    "comment_id" : 32079114,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "Often it is not too hard to rephrase things so that a plural &quot;all&quot; becomes a singular &quot;any&quot; with a negated result (e.g. De Morgan&#39;s laws). <code>areAllStoresClosed()</code> --&gt; <code>isAnyStoreOpen()</code> or <code>areAllStoresOpen()</code> --&gt; <code>isAnyStoreClosed()</code>"
  } ],
